PRIVACY POLICY

Permissions Inspector

Last Updated: June 2026

1. Introduction

Welcome to Permissions Inspector ("App", "Service", "we", "our", or "us").

Permissions Inspector is an Android application designed to help users understand, inspect, monitor, and analyze permissions granted to applications installed on their devices. The App provides visibility into installed applications, their permissions, usage characteristics, and related privacy insights to assist users in making informed decisions regarding application privacy and security.

We are committed to transparency and responsible handling of information. This Privacy Policy explains what information is accessed, how it is used, and the choices available to users.

By downloading, installing, accessing, or using Permissions Inspector, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

2. Information Accessed and Processed

Permissions Inspector is designed to minimize data collection and primarily performs analysis directly on the user's device.

2.1 Installed Applications Information

To provide its core functionality, Permissions Inspector may access information about applications installed on your device, including:

• Application names
• Package names
• Application icons
• Application versions
• Permission declarations
• Granted permissions
• Permission groups
• Application metadata available through Android APIs
• Application categories where available

This information is used solely to provide application permission auditing, privacy analysis, risk indicators, and security-related insights.

2.2 Usage Statistics Information

If you voluntarily grant Android Usage Access permission, the App may access usage statistics provided by the Android operating system, including:

• Application usage duration
• Application launch frequency
• Last usage timestamps
• Foreground activity information
• Aggregate application usage metrics

The App does not access the content of applications, communications, documents, web activity, messages, photos, videos, passwords, or personal files.

Usage statistics are used solely to:

• Display application usage insights
• Correlate application activity with permission exposure
• Generate privacy-related reports
• Assist users in evaluating application behavior

2.3 Device Information

The App may access limited device information including:

• Device manufacturer
• Device model
• Android version
• App version
• Screen characteristics
• Language settings

This information is used to improve compatibility, performance, and reliability.

2.4 Diagnostic Information

The App may collect diagnostic information including:

• Crash reports
• Error logs
• Performance metrics
• Technical diagnostics

This information helps improve application stability and performance.

3. QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES Permission

Permissions Inspector uses Android's QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES permission.

This permission is essential to the core functionality of the App because the primary purpose of Permissions Inspector is to inspect and analyze applications installed on the device.

The permission enables the App to:

• Discover installed applications
• Analyze application permissions
• Generate permission reports
• Provide application inventory analysis
• Display security and privacy insights
• Compare permissions across applications

Without QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES permission, Permissions Inspector cannot provide comprehensive permission auditing functionality.

Information obtained through this permission is used exclusively for the App's intended functionality as described in this Privacy Policy.

4. PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS (Usage Access)

Permissions Inspector may request Android Usage Access permission.

Granting Usage Access is optional and requires explicit user approval through Android settings.

When granted, the App may access usage statistics exposed by Android for the sole purpose of:

• Displaying application activity insights
• Enhancing privacy analysis
• Supporting permission risk assessments
• Providing user-requested usage reports

Permissions Inspector does not record keystrokes, capture screen contents, monitor communications, or access private content through Usage Access permission.

